## Comprehensive Deadlock Investigation Report: Kafka Streams

I've conducted a thorough investigation of the Kafka Streams source code and identified **multiple critical deadlock-prone patterns** involving circular lock dependencies. Here are my findings:

### CRITICAL DEADLOCK PATTERN #1: KafkaStreams.StreamStateListener - Synchronized Method Calling setState()

**File:** `/app/streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/KafkaStreams.java`
**Lines:** 649-676 (onChange method), 342-382 (setState method)

```java
// Line 649: Synchronized method
@Override
public synchronized void onChange(final Thread thread,
                                  final ThreadStateTransitionValidator abstractNewState,
                                  final ThreadStateTransitionValidator abstractOldState) {
    // StreamThreads first
    if (thread instanceof StreamThread) {
        final StreamThread.State newState = (StreamThread.State) abstractNewState;
        threadState.put(thread.getId(), newState);

        if (newState == StreamThread.State.PARTITIONS_REVOKED || newState == StreamThread.State.PARTITIONS_ASSIGNED) {
            setState(State.REBALANCING);  // Line 658: CALLS setState - which acquires stateLock
        } else if (newState == StreamThread.State.RUNNING) {
            maybeSetRunning();  // Line 660: Which calls setState
        }
    }
}

// Line 342-382: setState method
private boolean setState(final State newState) {
    final State oldState;
    synchronized (stateLock) {  // Line 345: Acquires stateLock
        // ... state transition logic ...
        state = newState;
        stateLock.notifyAll();
    }
    // Line 377: CALLS user code WHILE HOLDING stateLock indirectly through chain
    if (stateListener != null) {
        stateListener.onChange(newState, oldState);  
    }
    return true;
}
```

**Deadlock Scenario:**
- Thread A holds the `StreamStateListener` instance lock (synchronized method)
- Thread A calls `setState()` which acquires `stateLock`
- Thread B holds `stateLock`
- Thread B tries to call method on `StreamStateListener` and blocks on its lock
- **DEADLOCK** - Circular wait

---

### CRITICAL DEADLOCK PATTERN #2: StateDirectory - Multiple Synchronized Methods with Different Lock Objects

**File:** `/app/streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/StateDirectory.java`
**Lines:** 286-292 (removeStartupState), 500-533 (lock/unlock)

